{"author":{"id":"e4abb5775a91d786e33fea2e5d9cf6fb2dbca63fab80e2497fb26c109d8fa1c2"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1735528474,"nonce":"HkOZ4doi2bkp3MHqbNTkQHUPyCY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOJl1IZM6kqcfm","github-url":"https://github.com/nikitabobko/AeroSpace/issues/905","origin":"github"},"title":"Workspace 1 defaults to accordion on startup when default is tiles","message":"Description\n\nI am encountering an issue where Workspace 1 does not follow the default-root-container-layout = 'tiles' configuration in the aerospace.toml file. While all other workspaces are correctly using the 'tiles' layout, Workspace 1 defaults to the 'accordion' layout.\n\nInterestingly, I can manually switch Workspace 1 to the 'tiles' layout by using the shortcut (ctrl-alt-shift-slash = 'layout tiles horizontal vertical'), but this is not the expected behavior.\n\nSteps to Reproduce\n\t1.\tSet the default-root-container-layout = 'tiles' in the aerospace.toml configuration file.\n\t2.\tLaunch or switch to Workspace 1.\n\t3.\tObserve that Workspace 1 is still using the 'accordion' layout, even though the default is 'tiles'.\n\t4.\tManually use ctrl-alt-shift-slash = 'layout tiles horizontal vertical' to switch Workspace 1 to the 'tiles' layout.\n\nExpected Behavior\n\t•\tWorkspace 1 should automatically adopt the 'tiles' layout on startup or when switching, without needing to manually invoke the layout switch.\n\nActual Behavior\n\t•\tWorkspace 1 defaults to the 'accordion' layout, even though the default configuration is set to 'tiles'.\n\t•\tUsing the shortcut (ctrl-alt-shift-slash = 'layout tiles horizontal vertical') manually switches Workspace 1 to the correct 'tiles' layout.\n\nEnvironment Details\n\t•\tAeroSpace CLI client version: 0.16.2-Beta 21336ad382539b35fdc94b4fbd55408e10b101f8\n\t•\tAeroSpace.app server version: 0.16.2-Beta 21336ad382539b35fdc94b4fbd55408e10b101f8\n\t•\tOperating System: macOS\n\t•\tProductName: macOS\n\t•\tProductVersion: 15.2\n\t•\tBuildVersion: 24C101\n